The paper discusses a theoretical analysis of a Terminological Knowledge Representation System (TKRS) that extends the capabilities of existing TKRSs. The paper focuses on the expressiveness of the terminological language, the ability to express inclusion statements between general concepts, and the decidability of TKRS-deduction services. These topics are relevant to several sub-categories of computer science, including artificial intelligence (cs.AI), logic in computer science (cs.LO), databases (cs.DB), computational linguistics (cs.CL), and software engineering (cs.SE). Therefore, these are the most likely sub-categories for this paper.
